webpackJsonp([60123591190368],{1221:function(e,a){e.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<p>I didn’t get much work done this weekend, but in the previous days, I went through several demos for game creation software in an effort to try and choose a platform for game-design in my GDS Challenge. In the end, I found that they all will need more of a time investment to get really good with but, for now at least, I’m going with Construct 2 because it allows me to take my development on the road. Here are a few demos:</p>\n<h2>Phaser IO</h2>\n<p>The Phaser tutorial was really nice and I liked that they not only game you tutorial files but they showed you some other important game ideas like scoring. Development was fairly simple and output is HTML5.</p>\n<figure>\n  <a href="http://www.knanthony.com/showcase/gamedev/phaser/index.html" target="blank">\n    \n  <span class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper" style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">\n    <span class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image" style="padding-bottom: 75.12500000000001%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;">\n      <img class="gatsby-resp-image-image" style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;" alt="Phaser tutorial game" title="" src="/static/PhaserIOtutorial-823c94035e1bf0e62700f2bbf7d483e4-dc451.png" srcset="/static/PhaserIOtutorial-823c94035e1bf0e62700f2bbf7d483e4-09bd2.png 203w,\n/static/PhaserIOtutorial-823c94035e1bf0e62700f2bbf7d483e4-dfc90.png 405w,\n/static/PhaserIOtutorial-823c94035e1bf0e62700f2bbf7d483e4-dc451.png 800w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n  <figcaption>Phaser IO Tutorial file. Click to play</figcaption>\n</figure>\n<h2>Stencyl</h2>\n<p>Stencyl development was a little more difficult but I really like the layout of the workspace and game files. It’s really easy for me to find where everything is. Output (for an unpaid version at least) is a nicely compact flash file which makes it really easy to transport because you don’t have to worry about losing anything.</p>\n<figure>\n  <a href="http://www.knanthony.com/showcase/gamedev/stencyl/CrashCourseGame.swf" target="blank">\n    \n  <span class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper" style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 642px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">\n    <span class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image" style="padding-bottom: 60.59190031152648%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;">\n      <img class="gatsby-resp-image-image" style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;" alt="Stencyl tutorial game" title="" src="/static/Stencyltutorial-5816f4393de1b96f392e3e167194f21f-523ec.png" srcset="/static/Stencyltutorial-5816f4393de1b96f392e3e167194f21f-92217.png 203w,\n/static/Stencyltutorial-5816f4393de1b96f392e3e167194f21f-ecbf1.png 405w,\n/static/Stencyltutorial-5816f4393de1b96f392e3e167194f21f-523ec.png 642w" sizes="(max-width: 642px) 100vw, 642px">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n  <figcaption>Stencyl Tutorial file. Click to play</figcaption>\n</figure>\n<h2>Construct 2</h2>\n<p>Construct 2 probably gave me the most trouble development-wise and I’m not a huge fan of the workspace and game files layout. However, the output is really nice-looking HTML5 that seems to be responsive to window size, which makes it a great option for embedding in Storyline. The best thing, though, is that the program can be installed on a portable drive, allowing me to take game development with me, instead of being tied to one computer. The tutorial files were a little less helpful than Stencyl or Phaser IO but I’m (very, very slowly) getting the hang of it. Still, I don’t expect that my GDS Challenge will be anything remarkable.</p>\n<figure>\n  <a href="http://knanthony.com/showcase/gamedev/construct2/index.html" target="blank">\n    \n  <span class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper" style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 810px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">\n    <span class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image" style="padding-bottom: 53.71120107962213%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;">\n      <img class="gatsby-resp-image-image" style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;" alt="Construct 2 tutorial game" title="" src="/static/construct2tutorial-f7cccdf8dfbe6c5ae89dca753982f97d-1626e.png" srcset="/static/construct2tutorial-f7cccdf8dfbe6c5ae89dca753982f97d-076ec.png 203w,\n/static/construct2tutorial-f7cccdf8dfbe6c5ae89dca753982f97d-7ae34.png 405w,\n/static/construct2tutorial-f7cccdf8dfbe6c5ae89dca753982f97d-1626e.png 810w,\n/static/construct2tutorial-f7cccdf8dfbe6c5ae89dca753982f97d-9af38.png 1215w,\n/static/construct2tutorial-f7cccdf8dfbe6c5ae89dca753982f97d-78f43.png 1482w" sizes="(max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n  <figcaption>Made using Construct 2 tutorial. Click to play</figcaption>\n</figure>',frontmatter:{date:"June 15, 2015",path:"/blog/playing-games",title:"Playing Games: Experimenting with Game Makers",tags:["construct 2","game design","phaser io","stencyl"],categories:["Design","Showing my Work"],featured:{childImageSharp:{sizes:{base64:"data:image/png;base64,",aspectRatio:2,src:"/static/playing-games-e62c9f4e8b013cd1f7a9333a645106c9-81d39.png",srcSet:"/static/playing-games-e62c9f4e8b013cd1f7a9333a645106c9-9a8d1.png 203w,\n/static/playing-games-e62c9f4e8b013cd1f7a9333a645106c9-c53f9.png 405w,\n/static/playing-games-e62c9f4e8b013cd1f7a9333a645106c9-81d39.png 810w,\n/static/playing-games-e62c9f4e8b013cd1f7a9333a645106c9-fda19.png 1024w",sizes:"(max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px"}}}}}},pathContext:{}}}});
